<@U026PHQ3J> I think I came up with a solution for the parallax issue that is rather simple: Rather than increasing the size of the overlay in the crop activity, I simply set the overlay width to the size of the screen so that the user selects the exact area they want to focus on. Then, in `recomputeTransformMatrices()`, I removed the logic that centers the image inside the cropped area. The result is a perfectly centred image on the first page of the home screen and then with each scroll, it pans right in the original image. I will push this momentarily.
